h Jason Smith]]''.\n\n''[[Sports Illustrated]]'''s Richard Deitsch named him Best Radio Voice of 2007 for his work on ESPN Radio. He praised Russillo's \"reasoned approach and knowledge across sports.\"<ref name=UVM2010>{{cite news |title=RYEN RUSSILLO \u201997 - Talking Sports |url=http://alumni.uvm.edu/vq/summer2010/alumni.asp |work=The UVM Connection > Vermont Quarterly |publisher=University of Vermont |location=Burlington, Vermont |date=Summer 2010 |accessdate=2010-08-09}}</ref>\n\nHe appeared regularly on several shows on [[Comcast Sportsnet New England]], including ''New England Sports Tonight'' with Gary Tanguay and [[Greg Dickerson]], and was also a studio analyst for the [[Boston Celtics]]' television coverage.\n\nDuring the NBA season, Russillo was the host of ESPN's ''The NBA Today'' podcast, the network's #2 most downloaded podcast series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espnradio/podcast/archive?id=3634017|title=The Hoop Collective Show - PodCenter - ESPN Radio|website=ESPN Radio}}</ref> Contrary to popular belief, in December 2012, this show was not cancelled to be swapped out with ''NBA Lockdown'' featuring former NBA player [[Bruce Bowen]].\n\nIn September 2015, Russillo welcomed former [[National Football League|NFL]] player [[Danny Kanell]] as the new co-host for his ''Russillo Show'', after [[Scott Van Pelt]]'s departure from ESPN Radio. Kanell was laid off from ESPN in April 2017, leaving Russillo as the sole host again, with multiple guest co-hosts occasionally joining him on the show.\n\nOn December 20, 2017, Russillo announced he was leaving his ESPN radio show to pursue other opportunities, with his final radio show taking place on December 22.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/tech-media/2017/12/20/ryen-russillo-leaving-espn-radio|title=Ryen Russillo Leaving ESPN Radio|website=si.com|first=Jimmy|last=Traina|date=December 20, 2017|accessdate=January 24, 2018}}</ref> Since departing his show, he has continued to produce a podcast with ESPN and has also been appearing across several ESPN platforms including on television with ''[[Get Up! (ESPN program)|Get Up!]]''. In late August 2018 he re-signed with ESPN.<ref>{{cite web |first= Phillip |last=Bupp |url=http://awfulannouncing.com/ringer/ryen-russillo-sets-his-future-announcing-new-espn-deal-and-a-new-podcast-with-the-ringer.html |title=Ryen Russillo sets his future announcing new ESPN deal and a new podcast with The Ringer |date=August 24, 2018|website=Awful Announcing }}</ref>\n\nIn June 2019 Russillo re-united with old colleague Scott Van Pelt on the \"SVP & Russillo\" podcast.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laughingplace.com/w/news/2019/05/30/former-espn-radio-hosts-scott-van-pelt-and-ryen-russillo-to-reunite-for-new-podcast/|title=Former ESPN Radio Hosts Scott Van Pelt and Ryen Russillo to Reunite for New Podcast|last=Newsdesk|first=Laughing Place Disney|date=2019-05-30|website=LaughingPlace.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/186791/espn-audio-sets-june-3rd-debut-for-reunited-svp-ru|title=ESPN Audio Sets June 3rd Debut For Reunited 'SVP & Russillo' Show As Podcast|website=All Access|language=en|access-date=2019-06-18}}</ref>\n\nOn August 5th, 2019, Russillo announced on his [[Twitter]] account that he would be leaving [[ESPN]] at the end of August and would be joining [[The Ringer (website)|The Ringer]] as a full time media personality.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ryenarussillo/status/1158553945255505920|title=So...the news is out. I\u2019m headed to @ringer want to thank @espn for the last 14 years. I grew up on @SportsCenter and then to be on the actual set, my name on a show...have to remind myself at times how cool that is. Excited to try and limit Celts talk to 30mins w/ @BillSimmons|last=Russillo|date=2019-08-05|website=@ryenarussillo|language=en|access-date=2019-08-07}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nOn August 23, 2017, Russillo was arrested in Wyoming for criminal entry, reportedly while nude and intoxicated.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/more-sports/espn-ryen-russillo-arrested-criminal-entry-charge-article-1.3436269|title=ESPN Radio host Ryen Russillo arrested after police find him drunk and naked in stranger's condo: report|newspaper=[[New York Daily News]]|last=Bodner|first=Brett|date=23 August 2017}}</ref> He was suspended by ESPN.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/4465343/ryen-russillo-reportedly-suspended-by-espn-after-wyoming-arrest/|title=ESPN Radio host Ryen Russillo suspended after police find him drunk and naked in stranger's condo: report|work=[[Inquisitr]]|date=August 28, 2017|author=Robert Jonathan}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://espnmediazone.com/us/bios/russillo_ryen/ ESPN bio]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Russillo, Ryen}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American radio journalists]]\n[[Category:American sports journalists]]\n[[Category:Baseball announcers]]\n[[Category:College football announcers]]\n[[Category:ESPN people]]\n[[Category:National Football League announcers]]\n[[Category:New England Patriots broadcasters]]\n[[Category:People from West Tisbury, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:University of Vermont alumni]]\n", "name_user": "Ira Leviton", "label": "safe", "comment": "Deleted a duplicate \"the\".", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ryen_Russillo"}
